Dourine, Italy
--------------
Information received on 14 Jun 2011 from Prof. Dr. Romano Marabelli,
Chief Veterinary Officer, Department for Veterinary Public Health,
Nutrition and Food Safety, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 27 May 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 01 Jun 2011
Report date 14 Jun 2011
Date submitted to OIE 14 Jun 2011
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 1996
Manifestation of disease Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent Trypanosoma equiperdum
Nature of diagnosis Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (3 Dourine) Frattamaggiore, Napoli, Campania
Date of start of the outbreak 27 May 2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Farm
Affected animals
Species Equidae
Susceptible 8
Cases 2
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0

Epidemiology - Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection.
Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures - Measures applied. Quarantine; Movement control
inside the country; Screening; Modified stamping out; No
vaccination; No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied - No other measures

Laboratory name and type: Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute
(IZS), Teramo (National laboratory)
Species Equidae
Test complement fixation test (CFT)
Test date 01 Jun 2011
Result Positive

Species Equidae
Test direct immunofluorescence (DIF) test
Test date 01 Jun 2011
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

